r\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"divider\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"8ecb02d\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"58a5eb7\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100,\"_inline_size\":null},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"292167c\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p><em>When Bhavin Ustadiya weaved together embroidery and e-commerce, he gave a new spin to a family business started by his father. Soon, Fabcartz was born. When his younger brother Yogesh also joined the business, the small venture created a niche of its own, specializing in traditional fashion for women. Today, Fabcartz is home to a large family of employees keen on adopting digital commerce to bring the beauty of Surat to every home in the country! Read on.<\\/em><\\/p>\",\"text_color\":\"#0EB7FF\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"364cff8\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"a33aa57\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100,\"_inline_size\":null},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"0cba43e\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"image\":{\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/localhost\\/wordpress-3\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2023\\/03\\/Bhavin-Ustadiya_Main-Banner.png\",\"id\":120,\"size\":\"\",\"alt\":\"\",\"source\":\"library\"},\"width\":{\"unit\":\"%\",\"size\":100,\"sizes\":[]},\"space\":{\"unit\":\"%\",\"size\":100,\"sizes\":[]},\"css_filters_css_filter\":\"custom\",\"image_border_border\":\"solid\",\"image_border_color\":\"#FFFFFF\",\"image_border_radius\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"14\",\"right\":\"14\",\"bottom\":\"14\",\"left\":\"14\",\"isLinked\":false}},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"image\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"f8ab6c9\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"5ead9e7\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100,\"_inline_size\":null},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"ca2c90a\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p><span class=\\\"dropcaps one-class\\\">F<\\/span>rom humble beginnings in Surat, Gujarat, a close-knit family turned a small family business into a fast-growing fashion brand. It all started when\\u00a0<strong>Bhavin Ustadiya<\\/strong>\\u00a0decided to take his father\\u2019s embroidery trade to the next level. Seeing his father give the business his all, Bhavin felt he had to quit his regular job to develop his family trade.<\\/p><p>This was six years ago, when Bhavin was just beginning to hear a lot of buzz around e-commerce in India. When he learned more about the power of e-commerce, he was set on taking his family business beyond Surat. And\\u00a0<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/flipkart.com\\/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener\\\">Flipkart<\\/a>\\u00a0helped him do just that.<\\/p><p>Soon, what was once a small enterprise blossomed into Fabcartz, a brand offering traditional wear like sarees, half sarees, lehenga cholis, and dupattas. A civil engineering student, Bhavin\\u2019s younger brother Yogesh also had his heart set on the clothing industry. With the family business gaining momentum, Yogesh began to direct his creative potential to the world of fashion design.<\\/p><p>With inspiration from Yogesh, direction from Bhavin and blessings from their father, Fabcartz remains a traditional family business at heart. It has now expanded to a team of over 50, and work is celebrated every day. In fact, when work doubles and triples during The Big Billion Days sale, the Fabcartz family gets into festive mode, enjoying every bit of the art of achieving together.<\\/p><p>Read their heartwarming story in Bhavin\\u2019s own words.<\\/p>\",\"text_color\":\"#000000\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false}]'),
